# Critical invariants — 99trees (Zugvögel)

## Commits (STRICT)
- NEVER auto-commit — only commit on explicit user request ("commit", "committe das")
- NEVER skip hooks (`--no-verify`)
- NEVER force-push to main/master or tags

## Releases / tags
- If this repo uses tags for deploys, NEVER force-push tags
- Prefer release scripts (if present) over manual version bumps for production releases

## Security
- Secrets stay server-only (runtime config / env) — never ship secrets to the client bundle
- Do not read `.env`, `.env.*`, credential, token, or private-key files unless the user explicitly asks for a specific value or line
- Never commit `.env` files or credentials

